• Introduction: 
	Having spent mostly all my life in Vietnam before moving to Canada for school, I was fortunate enough to travel across the country to see how vast and eye-opening the Vietnamese landscape has to offer. With its fascinating history, gorgeous landscapes, tasty food, and vibrant energy, Vietnam will awaken all your senses and pull you in from all angles.

	I am interested in making this project because travelling has always been a strong passion of mine. One of my bucket lists is to travel the world and experience all the amazing food they have in each country.  My main inspiration in creating such a website is to introduce Vietnam to foreign friends around the world, in the hopes of boosting the Vietnamese economy, creating more jobs for the locals through tourism and hopefully improve the infrastructure of the country with the increasing number of tourists. I acknowledge to make this happen, a lot of time and effort has to be invested from the locals and the government. 

When I was planning for my trip to travel across Vietnam, I found it incredibly hard to find information about the destinations I wanted to visit on Vietnamese travel websites. Most travel websites to only allow booking and access for trips to famous and densely populated cities, such as the capital – Ha Noi or Ho Chi Minh City. I found this incredibly frustrating because there are so many potential travel locations not being easily accessible through travel tours. 

My main goal for creating the website in this project is to replicate a travel company who organizes trips to not just popular but also remote locations of Vietnam. My website is nowhere near perfect, it has a lot of room for improvements – however, it is a good starting point which I can use to attract my friends to choose Vietnam for their next travel destinations.

